							<div class="row">
								<div class="col-lg-12">
									<p class="text-justify">
										The Finance Minister, in his budget speech for 2016-17,
										announced the launch of new restructured scheme of <em>Rashtriya
											Gram Swaraj Abhiyan (RGSA)</em>, for developing and strengthening
										the capacities of Panchayati Raj Institutions (PRIs) for rural
										local governance to become more responsive towards local
										development needs, preparing the participatory plans that
										leverage technology, efficient and optimum utilization of
										available resources for realizing sustainable solutions to
										local problems linked to Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).
										The key principles of SDGs, i.e. leaving no one behind,
										reaching the farthest first and universal coverage, along with
										gender equality will be embedded in the design of all capacity
										building interventions including trainings, training modules
										and materials.
									</p>
									<p class="text-justify">
										In his Budget Speech for 2017-18, the Finance Minister
										announced to undertake a Mission Antyodaya to bring one crore
										households out of poverty to make 50,000 Gram Panchayats
										poverty free. Accordingly, convergent action with Mission
										Antyodaya has been integrated into this scheme.<br> <br>
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							<div class="row">
								<div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
